result.name: Discovery Bay Plaza

reviews.text: Nice place with good food and places to shop, would say it needs a fresh coat of paint (but where doesn't in Hong Kong with the humidity). The ferry (runs to Central) is easy to get to and runs I think every 30 minutes. Is you get a chance to go to the Korean place where you grill your own food, you must, fantastic food.
Great place overlooking the beach and close to ferry

Major commercial centre for Discovery Bay residents. Banks, supermarket, salon, department and grocery stores intend for maximum convenience. Residents and tourists never need to worry about food as there are numerous cuisine choices: Italian, Middle East, Mexican, BBQ, Chinese, bars and pubs. Fairs are also held for festival celebrations. Unfortunately the bus terminal and part of the shopping mall is under expansion which is expected to complete in 2019. Nevertheless old needs to go for new to come!  Look forward to the new look of DB Plaza!
Nice plaza and square. Plenty of restaurants with outdoor seating and some shops as well.
Europe style. A completely different feel, very relaxed.
